OL,3,CGovernment plans more benefit cuts as
OL,4,COBR downgrades welfare savings
OL,6,FMinisters claimed it was all about
OL,7,Fincentivising work (and not cutting
OL,8,Fmoney) but the OBR assessment told a
OL,9,Fdifferent story.
OL,11,FIt claimed that while over 400,000
OL,12,Fpeople would see their benefits cut,
OL,13,Fonly around 15,000 would move into
OL,14,Fwork.
OL,16,FSo, the OBR has a history of being
OL,17,Fsceptical about savings from changing
OL,18,Fbenefit threshold rules, and the
OL,19,Fpositive impact of employment
OL,20,Fincentives.
